HEADWORD: Tournure
<hw>Tour*nure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>tourner</ets> to turn.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Turn; contour; figure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any device used by women to expand the skirt of a
dress below the waist; a bustle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Touze</ent>⟦br⟧
